{{Short description|Maldivian politician}} {{BLP sources|date=December 2023}} <!--Please do not add mayor, He is noy yet mayor untill he inaugurates--> {{Use British English|date=April 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}} {{Infobox officeholder | honorific_prefix = [[Mayor-elect]][[Malé|of Malé]] | honorific_suffix = | name = Adam Azim | image = Adam_Azim_MTCC.jpg | profession = Politician | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Malé]], [[Maldives]] | death_date = | death_place = | alma_mater = [[University of Nottingham]] [[University of East London]] | caption = Azim in 2021 <!--| office1 = Mayor of [[Malé]] | succeeding1 = | status1 = [[Incumbent]] | term_start1 = 14 January 2024 | president1 = [[Mohamed Muizzu]] | predecessor1 = [[Ahmed Nareesh]] (acting mayor) --> | office2 = CEO of [[MTCC]] | successor2 = [[Mr. Abdulla Ziyad]] | term_start2 = 21 January 2020 | term_end2 = 17 November 2023 | president2 = | predecessor2 = }}
'''Adam Azim''' {{lang-dv|އާދަމް އާޒިމް}} is the [[mayor|Mayor-Elect]] of [[Malé]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Mohamed |first=Mariyath |date=13 January 2024 |title=Male' Mayoral Election: Azim wins by a large margin! |url=https://edition.mv/adam_azim/31003 |access-date=13 January 2024 |work=The Edition}}</ref> He is also the Chief Executive Officer of the [[State-owned enterprise|state owned enterprise]], [[Maldives Transport and Contracting Company (MTCC)]]. He was previously the Managing Director of the [[State Trading Organization]] (STO).<ref>{{cite web |author= |date= |title=Adam Azim - MTCC Board |url=https://mtcc.mv/our-board/adam-azim/ |website=MTCC}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Rehan |first=Mohamed |date=28 August 2022 |title=MTCC completes 90 projects in 3 years |url=https://edition.mv/adam_azim_md_mtcc/25615 |work=The Edition}}</ref>
