'''Adam Azim''' ({{lang-dv|އާދަމް އާޒިމް}}; born 17 December 1971) is a Maldivian politician who is currently serving as the [[Malé|Mayor of Malé]] since 22 January 2024.
He won the Mayoral Elections, defeating ruling party, [[People's National Congress (Maldives)|People's National Congress]]'s candidate, [[Azima Shukoor|Azima Shakoor]]. ==Career== Adam azim is the incumbent mayor of [[Malé]], the capital of the [[Maldives]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Maldives: Adam Azim from Maldivian Democratic Party wins Male mayoral by-election |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/maldives-adam-azim-from-maldivian-democratic-party-wins-male-mayoral-by-election/articleshow/106824670.cms?from=mdr |access-date=14 January 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Mohamed |first1=Mariyath |title=Adam Azim: New Mayor of Male' City |url=https://edition.mv/report/31005 |access-date=14 January 2024 |agency=edition}}</ref> He also served as the [[Chief executive officer]] of Maldives Transport and Contracting Company.<ref>{{cite news |title=Adam Azim, 5 Points On New Mayor Of Male From Pro India Party |url=https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/adam-azim-5-points-on-new-mayor-of-male-from-pro-india-party-4859569 |access-date=14 January 2024}}</ref> Azim also served as the Managing Director of [[State Trading Organization]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Adam Azim, CEO of Maldives Transport & Contracting Company |url=https://corporatemaldives.com/spotlight/adam-azim-ceo-of-maldives-transport-contracting-company/ |website=Corporate Maldives |access-date=10 April 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Adam Azim: The CEO Who Transformed MTCC into a Model Government Company |url=https://www.frontpage.mv/news/detail/740 |access-date=5 September 2023}}</ref> ==Mayoral Elections 2024== In Janyary 14, 2024 Azim was elected as the Mayor of [[Malé]] defeating [[People's National Congress (Maldives)|People's National Congress]]'s candidate, [[Azima Shukoor|Azima Shakoor]] with a vote of 7621, receiving 2590 votes more than his closest opponent, Azima Shakoor.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mohamed |first1=Mariyath |title=Male' Mayoral Election: Azim wins by a large margin! |url=htt